body:
@fanwu123 Can you reproduce this consistently? Does it happen on other devices as well?

@jrodbx yet another string parsing in heap dump problem? Not sure.. this is in API 19.

@pyricau Walking through the stack trace, the thread name returned [here](https://github.com/square/leakcanary/blob/b8e444b351bd2cdb46acd9ef1c707c5d9b64f172/leakcanary-analyzer/src/main/java/com/squareup/leakcanary/HahaHelper.java#L150) is null.
@fanwu123  Could you provide the heap dump that triggered this NPE?

You're right, I looked at it too fast. So the Thread class definitely had a name field, but that field was null. Which is in theory impossible, since Thread will throw if you try to create an instance with a null name.

but i have bad english, but at last i have provide  the heap dump.
the file i upload to baiduyun,if you can't download ,tell me your email,i will send to you
@fanwu123 Please upload and attach the heap dump to this issue using the comment textbox below.

Thx. We will look into the heap dump, see if there is anything interesting. We also want to check for null, with a comment explaining why.
